<h1>Food</h1>
<br />
<p>
  Sometimes cities have a food that is all their own: the Philly Cheesesteak, Chicago-Style pizza, a Primanti Brothers sandwich in Pittsburgh. Well in Minneapolis we have the <span class="strong">Jucy Lucy</span> (or Juicy Lucy depending on who you ask). When everyone else was foolishly putting cheese on top of their burgers, a brave Minneapolitan said, "No....that is wrong" and put the cheese <span class="strong">inside</span> (!) the burger (whaaaaaat!)
</p>
<br />
<p>
  Accounts differ as to who that actually was, but the three favorite places to get them are at <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "Matt's Bar", "http://www.mattsbar.com/index-1.html"%></span> (Minneapolis), the <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "5-8 Club", "http://www.5-8club.com/"%></span> (Minneapolis), and <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "The Nook", "http://www.crnook.com/"%></span> (St. Paul). None of these places is super close to downtown, unfortunately, so you may not be able to go unless you have some extra time to explore (and maybe a car). BUT, there are plenty of places <span class="content-link"><%= link_to "downtown", "http://www.yelp.com/search?find_desc=juicy+lucy&find_loc=Downtown+Minneapolis,+Minneapolis,+MN", target: "_blank" %></span> where you can try one...which you should.</p>
